# /.MEMORY/.aidocs/index.aidocs - Documentation Index

This file routes to the memory-system-local documentation that applies across projects.

Inside initialized projects, this is the session-start documentation entry point.

Router policy: this file is a link/list router only. Do not treat it as a forced full-load import list.

Read order when reached directly:
1. Stay in this file first.
2. Read `/.MEMORY/NOW.md`.
3. Read `/.MEMORY/INDEX.md`.
4. Open only task-relevant linked files.

## Core Setup Docs
- `/.MEMORY/.aidocs/index.aidocs`
- `/.MEMORY/.aidocs/global-instructions.aidocs`
- `/.MEMORY/.aidocs/coding-standards.aidocs`
- `/.MEMORY/.aidocs/memory-system.aidocs`

These files must exist in initialized projects. `/project-update` rewrites them from the AIDOCS source root.

## Runtime Routers
- `/.MEMORY/NOW.md`
- `/.MEMORY/INDEX.md`
- `/.MEMORY/CHANGELOG.md`

## Shared Docs
- `/.MEMORY/.aidocs/global-instructions.aidocs`
- `/.MEMORY/.aidocs/coding-standards.aidocs`
- `/.MEMORY/.aidocs/memory-system.aidocs`
- `/.MEMORY/.aidocs/research-safety.aidocs`
- `/.MEMORY/.aidocs/project-init.aidocs`
- `/.MEMORY/.aidocs/project-update.aidocs`
- `/.MEMORY/.aidocs/personality-system.aidocs`
- `/.MEMORY/.aidocs/reingest-system.aidocs`
- `/.MEMORY/.aidocs/cleanup-system.aidocs`

## Project-Specific Docs
Each project should add its own documentation index and link it here as it is created.
Use `/project-init` to initialize a new project.
Use `/project-update` to sync system files in already initialized projects.
